# Next.js RSC and Client Boundary Guards

Use this ESLint fragment:

```json
{
  "plugins": ["@next/next", "react"],
  "rules": {
    "no-restricted-syntax": [
      "error",
      {
        "selector": "BlockStatement > ExpressionStatement:has(AwaitExpression) ~ ExpressionStatement:has(AwaitExpression)",
        "message": "Potential RSC Data Waterfall detected. Wrap independent fetch requests in Promise.all()."
      },
      {
        "selector": "Program:has(ExpressionStatement > Literal[value='use client']) ExportNamedDeclaration > VariableDeclaration > VariableDeclarator > CallExpression[callee.name='createContext']",
        "message": "Client Boundary Contagion: Do not export Context Providers from generic client files. Isolate them in dedicated Provider components."
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

Parallelize independent data fetches and keep context providers isolated in dedicated client provider modules.
